Putin said that negotiations on Donbass are at a dead end
21 February 2022, 18:50
Photo: ©
kremlin.ru
Read ren.tv in
The negotiation process on Donbass has reached a dead end. Russian President Vladimir Putin announced this at a meeting of the Russian Security Council in the Kremlin.
Putin recalled that these negotiations have been going on for eight years.
“As for the negotiation process, then (Deputy Head of the Presidential Administration of the Russian Federation Dmitry - Hereinafter approx.
REN TV
) Kozak reported. It (the negotiation process) is at a dead end. Just a dead end. We have been negotiating for eight years. That's what we're talking about"
, Putin said.
Putin: The decision to recognize the DPR and LPR will be made today
Expand
21 February 2022, 18:29
Let us remind you that the DPR and LPR declared their independence in 2014 after the coup in Ukraine. For eight years, the authorities of the unrecognized republics tried to resolve the conflict. However, Kiev did not fulfill the requirements to de-escalate the conflict, ignoring the calls of Russia, Germany, and France - all members of the Normandy format.
The negotiation process was developed on the basis of the Minsk agreements, but the Ukrainian authorities made no attempts to implement them. In recent months, Kiev has openly refused to implement key points.
State Duma deputies appealed to the president with a request to recognize the independence of the LPR and DPR. This happened against the backdrop of aggravation of the situation in these republics.
Head of the DPR Denis Pushilin February 18
stated
that Ukrainian troops are ready to launch an offensive in Donbass. On the same day, the heads of the LPR and DPR
announced
on the evacuation of the population to Russia. On February 19, the leaders of the republics announced general mobilization.
February 21, heads of the DPR and LPR
contacted
to Russian President Vladimir Putin with a request to recognize the independence of the republics.
