In Russia
More than a thousand refugees from Donbass received payments
21 February 2022, 09:37
Photo: ©
RIA Novosti/Ilya Pitalev
Read ren.tv in
About four thousand applications for opening personal accounts to receive one-time financial assistance were completed within 24 hours by evacuees from the self-proclaimed Donetsk and Lugansk People's Republics (DPR and LPR). More than a thousand have already received payments, said the acting head of the Russian Ministry of Emergency Situations, Alexander Chupriyan.
“We have received about 4 thousand applications. And more than 1 thousand people have already received money. I am sure that in the near future this figure will increase significantly”
, he noted.
On February 18, President of the Russian Federation Vladimir Putin instructed
pay
10 thousand rubles for each refugee who arrived in the Rostov region from Donbass. At temporary accommodation centers to speed up receipt of payments
will put
mobile ATMs. People started receiving money on Sunday, February 20th.
The situation in Donbass
February 17 in LPR
stated
about the aggravation of the situation on the contact line. The same information came from the DPR. They noted that the Armed Forces of Ukraine 15 times since the beginning of the day
violated the "silence regime".
February 18, heads of the DPR and LPR
announced
about the beginning of temporary mass evacuation of the population to Russia. First of all, the evacuation concerns women, children and the elderly. February 19, heads of the DPR and LPR
announced
general mobilization.
In Russia, the Rostov region accepts most of the refugees - temporary accommodation centers have been created there.
Later 26 regions of Russia
declared their readiness to accept refugees
in temporary accommodation centers. About 2 thousand refugees were taken by train from the Rostov region to the Voronezh and Kursk regions.
As of February 21, to Russia
more than 61 thousand residents of Donbass arrived.
Let us recall that Ukraine’s military operation against the DPR and LPR began in 2014, after the regions declared independence in connection with the coup d’etat in the country. According to the UN, about 13 thousand people became victims of the clash.
